feat: Implement chat threads feature to replace singular chat history.

When a user message is received the assistant now checks for a relevant chat thread with the user in that specific room. If none is found then a new thread is started.

fix: Reject unwanted invitations.

Previously, unwanted invitations due to unallowed domains, non-beta users, or non-DM were not rejected. This left hanging invitations in the system.

feat: Implemented a logging gateway to replace print statements.

Messages in Gloria are now logged using the built-in Python logging module by default.

feat: Filter DM invitations by server domain.

This feature will ensure that users from third party federated servers can only interact with the assistant if the server domain is in the allowed list.

feat: Implemented limited beta functionality.
